"use strict";(self.webpackChunkdocsaur_ian=self.webpackChunkdocsaur_ian||[]).push([[1477],{10:n=>{n.exports=JSON.parse('{"blogPosts":[{"id":"json-file-handling","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/json-file-handling","editUrl":"https://github.com/fineon/fineon.github.io/tree/main/blog/json-file-handling.md","source":"@site/blog/json-file-handling.md","title":"A simple utility script to combine two JSON files together","description":"So I have been working on some REST API and JSON. One of the task that had to be done was how to manage multiple people editing a single API data point. So I came up with an idea of splitting a single JSON API data file into multiple files called \u201cfragments\u201d. Each \u201cfragment\u201d will hold a smaller amount of data created by a single author or contributor. The fragments will always adhere to the JSON data schema of course. Here\u2019s an example of a JSON file as the API data. This fragment is named api-data.json","date":"2022-07-24T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"July 24, 2022","tags":[{"label":"json","permalink":"/blog/tags/json"},{"label":"nodejs","permalink":"/blog/tags/nodejs"}],"readingTime":2.37,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Ian Nguyen","title":"Author","url":"https://github.com/fineon","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"json-file-handling","title":"A simple utility script to combine two JSON files together","author":"Ian Nguyen","author_title":"Author","author_url":"https://github.com/fineon","author_image_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4","date":"2022-07-24T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["json","nodejs"]},"nextItem":{"title":"H\xe3y nh\u1edb r\u1eb1ng n\u1ed7i \u0111au ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi","permalink":"/blog/hay-nho-rang-noi-dau-chi-la-nhat-thoi"}},"content":"So I have been working on some REST API and JSON. One of the task that had to be done was how to manage multiple people editing a single API data point. So I came up with an idea of splitting a single JSON API data file into multiple files called \u201cfragments\u201d. Each \u201cfragment\u201d will hold a smaller amount of data created by a single author or contributor. The fragments will always adhere to the JSON data schema of course. Here\u2019s an example of a JSON file as the API data. This fragment is named `api-data.json`\\r\\n\\r\\n```js\\r\\n[ //Array can hold multiple objects\\r\\n    { //Object\\r\\n        \\"year\\": \\"2329\\", //\\"string\\". Only one value\\r\\n        \\"allContinents\\": [ //Array can hold multiple objects\\r\\n            { //Object. Only contain the below keys/values\\r\\n                \\"continent\\": \\"asia\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                \\"country\\": \\"malaysia\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                \\"events\\": [ //array. Can hold multiple objects\\r\\n                    { // Object. Can only contain the below keys/values\\r\\n                        \\"event\\": \\"launched the first teleportation as a service\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                        \\"date\\": \\"3320-2-10\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                        \\"image\\": \\"\\", // string. Only one value \\r\\n                        \\"video\\": \\"\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                        \\"links\\": [ //Array. Can hold multiple strings\\r\\n                            \\"\\"\\r\\n                        ]\\r\\n                    },\\r\\n                    { // Object. Can only contain the below keys/values\\r\\n                        \\"event\\": \\"launched the first teleportation as a service\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                        \\"date\\": \\"3320-2-10\\", // string. Only one value YYYY-MM-DD\\r\\n                        \\"image\\": \\"https://i.imgur.com/dBm6h3p.png\\", // string. Only one value \\r\\n                        \\"video\\": \\"\\", // string. Only one value\\r\\n                        \\"links\\": [ //Array. Can hold multiple strings\\r\\n                            \\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teleportation\\",\\r\\n                            \\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Teleportation\\"\\r\\n                        ]\\r\\n                    },\\r\\n                ]\\r\\n            }\\r\\n        ]\\r\\n    }\\r\\n]\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nTo include newer JSON data, I created a javascript file to process the data, concatenate everything and write to a new file. Let\u2019s call this file `data-processing.js`\\r\\n\\r\\nAll of the JSON data fragments are in the `fragments` folder.\\r\\n\\r\\n```js\\r\\n/**\\r\\n * All data files should have all continent and country names in lowercase\\r\\n * all data fragment files will merged into the main data.json file\\r\\n *\\r\\n *\\r\\n */\\r\\nconst { allYearsAllLocation } = require(\\"../pages/api/api-data.json\\");\\r\\nconst fs = require(\\"fs/promises\\");\\r\\n\\r\\n//read and parse JSON data files\\r\\nlet dataString = JSON.stringify(allYearsAllLocation);\\r\\n\\r\\n//read dir => require all JSON files => parse all => flat merge all arrays => write to data.json file\\r\\nlet dataArr = [];\\r\\nlet allFragmentNames = [];\\r\\n\\r\\nconst readFilesAll = async () => {\\r\\n  try {\\r\\n\\t\\t// Read and return all of the files\' names\\r\\n    let fileNames = await fs.readdir(\\"./fragments\\");\\r\\n\\r\\n    dataArr = [...fileNames];\\r\\n\\r\\n    dataArr.forEach((item) => {\\r\\n      allFragmentNames.push(require(\\"./fragments/\\" + item));\\r\\n    });\\r\\n\\r\\n    let flattened = allFragmentNames.flat();\\r\\n    let mergeAll = allYearsAllLocation.concat(flattened);\\r\\n\\r\\n    let writeAll = await fs.writeFile(\\"./data.json\\", JSON.stringify(mergeAll));\\r\\n\\r\\n    //will return undefined upon successful write\\r\\n    console.log(writeAll);\\r\\n  } catch (error) {\\r\\n    console.log(error);\\r\\n  }\\r\\n};\\r\\n\\r\\nreadFilesAll();\\r\\n```\\r\\n\\r\\nAfter writing the script to handle JSON files and file editing, I can run the `data-processing.js` in Node.js runtime environment: `node data-processing.js`\\r\\n\\r\\nI will now see a new JSON file with the new data combined."},{"id":"hay-nho-rang-noi-dau-chi-la-nhat-thoi","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/hay-nho-rang-noi-dau-chi-la-nhat-thoi","editUrl":"https://github.com/fineon/fineon.github.io/tree/main/blog/Ha\u0303y-nho\u031b\u0301-ra\u0306\u0300ng-no\u0302\u0303i-\u0111au-chi\u0309-la\u0300-nha\u0302\u0301t-tho\u031b\u0300i.md","source":"@site/blog/Ha\u0303y-nho\u031b\u0301-ra\u0306\u0300ng-no\u0302\u0303i-\u0111au-chi\u0309-la\u0300-nha\u0302\u0301t-tho\u031b\u0300i.md","title":"H\xe3y nh\u1edb r\u1eb1ng n\u1ed7i \u0111au ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi","description":"This article first appeared on Spiderum, translated from a piece on Thought Catalog. References are at the bottom of the article.","date":"2021-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 14, 2021","tags":[{"label":"translation","permalink":"/blog/tags/translation"},{"label":"vietnamese","permalink":"/blog/tags/vietnamese"}],"readingTime":3.85,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Ian Nguyen","title":"Author","url":"https://github.com/fineon","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hay-nho-rang-noi-dau-chi-la-nhat-thoi","title":"H\xe3y nh\u1edb r\u1eb1ng n\u1ed7i \u0111au ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi","author":"Ian Nguyen","author_title":"Author","author_url":"https://github.com/fineon","author_image_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4","date":"2021-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["translation","vietnamese"]},"prevItem":{"title":"A simple utility script to combine two JSON files together","permalink":"/blog/json-file-handling"},"nextItem":{"title":"S\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\u1ee9 ti\u1ebfp di\u1ec5n nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o?","permalink":"/blog/su-co-don-cu-tiep-dien-nhu-the-nao"}},"content":"*This article first appeared on [Spiderum](https://spiderum.com/bai-dang/Hay-nho-rang-noi-dau-chi-la-nhat-thoi-66t), translated from a piece on [Thought Catalog](https://thoughtcatalog.com/marisa-donnelly/2017/04/pain-is-only-temporary-remember-that/). References are at the bottom of the article.*\\n\\nV\u1ea1n v\u1eadt l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi: t\u1eeb nh\u1eefng trang s\xe1ch b\u1ea1n \u0111ang \u0111\u1ecdc. Chi\u1ebfc gh\u1ebf b\u1ea1n \u0111ang ng\u1ed3i. B\u1ea7u tr\u1eddi xanh bi\u1ebfc s\u1edbm t\xe0n v\xe0o \u0111\xeam khuya. N\u1ee5 h\xf4n n\u1ed3ng \u1ea5m tr\xean m\xe1 b\u1ea1n. C\u01a1n gi\xf3 tho\u1ea3ng tr\xean c\xe2y. Nh\u1eefng c\xe1i ch\u1ea1m nh\u1eb9 nh\xe0ng t\u1eeb ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u1ea5y.\\n\\n*T\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u tr\xean ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 t\u1ea1m th\u1eddi*. C\u1ea3 nh\u1eefng kho\u1ea3nh kh\u1eafc tuy\u1ec7t \u0111\u1eb9p tho\xe1ng qua l\xfac b\u1ea1n thay \u0111\u1ed5i v\xe0 tr\u01b0\u1edfng th\xe0nh. T\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 nh\u1eefng c\u01a1n \u0111au \u0111\u1ea7u, kh\u1ed5 s\u1edf, tan v\u1ee1 \u0111\u1ec1u s\u1ebd h\xf2a tan nh\u01b0 gi\u1ecdt s\u01b0\u01a1ng v\xe0o m\u1ed7i s\xe1ng s\u1edbm.\\n\\n\u0110\xf4i l\xfac m\u1ecdi th\u1ee9 c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y th\u1eadt gh\xea s\u1ee3 khi ch\xfang ta m\u01b0\u1eddng t\u01b0\u1ee3ng m\u1ed9t th\u1ebf gi\u1edbi th\u1eadt kh\xe1c v\u1edbi th\u1ebf gi\u1edbi ch\xfang ta \u0111ang c\u01b0 ng\u1ee5, khi ch\xfang ta t\u1ef1 h\u1ecfi v\u1ec1 n\u01a1i ch\u1ed1n khi ch\xfang ta kh\xf4ng c\xf2n tr\xean m\u1eb7t \u0111\u1ea5y n\xe0y n\u1eefa, khi ch\xfang ta c\u0169ng ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi.\\n\\nNghe t\u01b0\u1edfng ch\u1eebng th\u1eadt \u0111\xe1ng s\u1ee3 nh\u01b0ng th\u1ef1c k\u1ef3 n\xf3 c\u0169ng th\u1eadt \xeam d\u1ecbu bi\u1ebft bao. V\xec n\xf3 nh\u1eafc nh\u1edf ch\xfang ta r\u1eb1ng d\xf9 ch\xfang ta c\xf3 tr\u1ea3i qua chuy\u1ec7n g\xec \u0111i ch\u0103ng n\u1eefa, d\xf9 tr\xe1i tim ta c\xf3 ch\u1ecbu \u0111au kh\u1ed5 ra sao, d\xf9 ch\xfang ta c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y m\u1ec7t m\u1ecfi v\xe0 ch\xe1n ch\u01b0\u1eddng nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o - Nh\u1eefng \u01b0u phi\u1ec1n \u0111\xf3 s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i m\xe3i m\xe3i.\\n\\n*N\u1ed7i \u0111au\xa0ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi.*\\n\\nH\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng mu\u1ed1n m\u1edf \u0111\xf4i m\u1eaft m\xecnh. H\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi \u0111\u1ee9a b\u1ea1n th\xe2n c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n ch\u1ea1y v\xe8o nhanh t\u1edbi b\xe0n \u0103n \u0111\u1ec3 b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 ng\u1ed3i xu\u1ed1ng. H\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng c\xf3 ai \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111i d\u1ea1 h\u1ed9i, khi b\u1ecb b\u1ecf r\u01a1i, khi b\u1ea1n b\u1eaft g\u1eb7p ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u1ea5y nh\u1eafn tin m\u1ed9t ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c.\\n\\nH\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi b\xe0 b\u1ea1n tr\xfat h\u01a1i th\u1edf cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng. H\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi b\u1ea1n ph\u1ea3i ti\u1ec5n \u0111\u01b0a ch\xfa ch\xf3 c\u1ee7a m\xecnh. H\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi m\u1ed9t ng\u01b0\u1eddi b\u1ea1n tin t\u01b0\u1edfng d\u1ed1i tr\xe1 v\xe0 b\u1ea1n th\u1ea5y m\xecnh th\u1eadt ngu ng\u1ed1c v\xec tin n\xf3. H\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi h\xf4n nh\xe2n c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ed5 v\u1ee1, khi con b\u1ea1n b\u1ecb g\xe3y tay, khi b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng ch\u1eafc n\xean tin ai hay c\xe1i g\xec. H\xe3y nh\u1edb \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 khi b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng bi\u1ebft n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n c\xf3 d\u0169ng c\u1ea3m \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ed1i m\u1eb7t m\u1ed9t ng\xe0y n\u1eefa.\\n\\n## **H\xe3y nh\u1edb r\u1eb1ng nh\u1eefng c\u1ea3m x\xfac b\u1ea1n \u0111ang tr\u1ea3i qua s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i l\xe0 v\u0129nh c\u1eedu.**\\n\\nM\u1ecdi th\u1ee9 \u0111\u1ec1u l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi. Nh\u1eefng c\u01a1 th\u1ec3 v\u1eadt ch\u1ea5t n\xe0y. Nh\u1eefng c\u1ea3m x\xfac n\xe0y. Nh\u1eefng nh\u1ecbp tim n\xe0y. \u0110\xfang, n\xf3 th\u1eadt \u0111\xe1ng s\u1ee3. Nh\u01b0ng l\u1ea1i th\u1eadt t\u1ef1 do n\u1eefa. V\xec n\xf3 c\xf3 ngh\u0129a r\u1eb1ng ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng b\u1ecb r\xe0ng bu\u1ed9c m\xe3i m\xe3i. Ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ed5 v\u1ee1 m\xe3i m\xe3i. Ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng cam b\u1ee9c nh\u1eefng l\u1eddi l\u1ebd nghi\u1ec7t ng\xe3 v\xe0 h\xe0nh \u0111\u1ed9ng b\u1ea1o l\u1ef1c t\u1eeb nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi ch\xfang ta y\xeau qu\xed (ho\u1eb7c t\u1eebng y\xeau qu\xed).\\n\\nN\xf3 s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf m\xe3i m\xe3i. Ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng th\u1ee9c d\u1eady v\xe0 nh\u1edb ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u1ea5y m\xe3i m\xe3i. Ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng c\xf3 nh\u1eefng \xe1c m\u1ed9ng v\u1ec1 cha m\u1eb9 \u0111\xe3 m\u1ea5t hay b\u1ecb \xe1m \u1ea3nh b\u1edfi \xe1c qu\u1ef7 t\u1eeb t\u1ed9i l\u1ed7i c\u1ee7a ch\xfang ta. Ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd d\u1eebng gh\xe9t b\u1ea3n th\xe2n m\xecnh, cu\u1ed9c s\u1ed1ng hay s\u1ef1 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i c\u1ee7a m\xecnh n\u1eefa.\\n\\n*V\xec trong t\u01b0\u01a1ng lai, nh\u1eefng n\u1ed1i \u0111au c\u1ee7a ta s\u1ebd bi\u1ebfn v\xe0o d\u0129 v\xe3ng.*\\n\\nV\u1eady n\xean xin b\u1ea1n h\xe3y v\u1eefng l\xf2ng. D\xf9 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t ph\xfat. M\u1ed9t gi\u1edd, M\u1ed9t ng\xe0y n\u1eefa. T\xecm nh\u1eefng th\u1ee9 l\xe0m b\u1ea1n m\u1ec9m c\u01b0\u1eddi - c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t th\u1ee9 nh\u1ecf nh\u1eafn, hay l\xe0 m\u1ed9t th\u1ee9 g\xec \u0111\xf3 to l\u1edbn - v\xe0 h\xe3y gi\u1eef v\u1eefng v\xe0o nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u \u1ea5y. H\u1ecdc t\u1eebng gi\xe2y v\u1ec1 t\u1ea1i sao cu\u1ed9c \u0111\u1eddi th\u1eadt \u0111\xe1ng s\u1ed1ng v\xe0 nh\u1eafc nh\u1edf b\u1ea3n th\xe2n \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y khi b\u1ea1n b\u1eaft \u0111\u1ea7u qu\xean n\xf3.\\n\\n## **H\xe3y chi\u1ebfn \u0111\u1ea5u. T\u1ef1 nh\u1ee7 b\u1ea3n th\xe2n r\u1eb1ng b\u1ea1n *s\u1ebd*\xa0s\u1ed1ng s\xf3t. B\u1edfi v\xec b\u1ea1n *s\u1ebd* s\u1ed1ng s\xf3t.**\\n\\nM\u1ed9t ng\xe0y n\xe0o \u0111\xf3, n\u1ed7i \u0111au s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng c\xf2n. M\u1ed9t ng\xe0y n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y \u0111au th\u01b0\u01a1ng n\u1eefa. M\u1ed9t ng\xe0y n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd nh\xecn l\u1ea1i nh\u1eefng th\u1ee9 \u0111\xe3 l\xe0m (su\xfdt) t\u1ed5n th\u01b0\u01a1ng b\u1ea1n v\xe0 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd th\u1ea5y b\u1ea1n \u0111\xe3 tr\u01b0\u1edfng th\xe0nh nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o. C\xe1ch b\u1ea1n \u0111\xe3 v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua n\xf3. C\xe1ch b\u1ea1n \u0111\xe3 qu\xe1 r\u1eddi xa b\xf3ng t\u1ed1i \u0111\u1ebfn n\u1ed7i b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 nh\u1edb \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c c\u1ea3m gi\xe1c khi r\u1eddi xa \xe1nh s\xe1ng.\\n\\nM\u1ed9t ng\xe0y n\xe0o \u0111\xf3 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd th\u1ea5y r\u1eb1ng n\u1ed7i \u0111au ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi, v\xe0 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd th\u1ea5y r\u1eb1ng b\u1ea1n lu\xf4n lu\xf4n c\xf3 s\u1ee9c m\u1ea1nh b\xean trong \u0111\u1ec3 v\u01b0\u1ee3t qua m\u1ecdi th\u1ee9.\\n\\nNgu\u1ed3n: **[Thought Catalog](http://thoughtcatalog.com/marisa-donnelly/2017/04/pain-is-only-temporary-remember-that/)**."},{"id":"su-co-don-cu-tiep-dien-nhu-the-nao","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/su-co-don-cu-tiep-dien-nhu-the-nao","editUrl":"https://github.com/fineon/fineon.github.io/tree/main/blog/Su\u031b\u0323-co\u0302-\u0111o\u031bn-cu\u031b\u0301-tie\u0302\u0301p-die\u0302\u0303n-nhu\u031b-the\u0302\u0301-na\u0300o.md","source":"@site/blog/Su\u031b\u0323-co\u0302-\u0111o\u031bn-cu\u031b\u0301-tie\u0302\u0301p-die\u0302\u0303n-nhu\u031b-the\u0302\u0301-na\u0300o.md","title":"S\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\u1ee9 ti\u1ebfp di\u1ec5n nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o?","description":"This article first appeared on Spiderum as one of my Vietnamese translation piece that accumulated over 1300 views.","date":"2021-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 14, 2021","tags":[{"label":"translation","permalink":"/blog/tags/translation"},{"label":"vietnamese","permalink":"/blog/tags/vietnamese"}],"readingTime":13.345,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Ian Nguyen","title":"Author","url":"https://github.com/fineon","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"su-co-don-cu-tiep-dien-nhu-the-nao","title":"S\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\u1ee9 ti\u1ebfp di\u1ec5n nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o?","author":"Ian Nguyen","author_title":"Author","author_url":"https://github.com/fineon","author_image_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4","date":"2021-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["translation","vietnamese"]},"prevItem":{"title":"H\xe3y nh\u1edb r\u1eb1ng n\u1ed7i \u0111au ch\u1ec9 l\xe0 nh\u1ea5t th\u1eddi","permalink":"/blog/hay-nho-rang-noi-dau-chi-la-nhat-thoi"},"nextItem":{"title":"Why I Switched from OneNote to Notion","permalink":"/blog/why-i-switched-from-onenote-to-notion"}},"content":"*This article first appeared on [Spiderum](https://spiderum.com/bai-dang/Su-co-don-cu-tiep-dien-nhu-the-nao-8ml) as one of my Vietnamese translation piece that accumulated over 1300 views.*\\n\\n![https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1472566316349-bce77aa2a778?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=85&fm=jpg&crop=entropy&cs=srgb](https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1472566316349-bce77aa2a778?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=85&fm=jpg&crop=entropy&cs=srgb)\\n\\n\\"R\xf5 r\xe0ng, t\xf4i l\xe0 m\u1ed9t tr\u01b0\u1eddng h\u1ee3p \u0111i\u1ec3n h\xecnh trong d\xe2n s\u1ed1 nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u0111\xe0n \xf4ng trung tu\u1ed5i - nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xf4ng mu\u1ed1n th\u1eeba nh\u1eadn r\u1eb1ng h\u1ecd mong mu\u1ed1n m\u1ed9t t\xecnh b\u1ea1n, k\u1ec3 c\u1ea3 khi t\u1ea5t c\u1ea3 c\xe1c d\u1ea5u hi\u1ec7u ch\u1ec9 \u0111i\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1ee3c l\u1ea1i,\\" tr\xedch Billy Baker v\u1ec1 h\xe0nh tr\xecnh kh\xe1m ph\xe1 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\u1ee7a ph\xe1i \u0111\xe0n \xf4ng tr\xean t\u1edd The Boston Globe.\\n\\nC\xf3 l\u1ebd l\xfd do t\u1ea1i sao b\xe0i vi\u1ebft c\u1ee7a \xf4ng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ph\xe1t t\xe1n tr\xean c\u1ed9ng \u0111\u1ed3ng m\u1ea1ng nhi\u1ec1u \u0111\u1ebfn th\u1ebf l\xe0 v\xec h\u1ecd c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ed3ng c\u1ea3m: N\u0103m ngo\xe1i, nh\xe0 ph\u1eabu thu\u1eadt Vivek Murthy c\u1ea3nh b\xe1o r\u1eb1ng ng\u01b0\u1eddi M\u1ef9 \u0111ang \\"\u0111\u1ed1i di\u1ec7n m\u1ed9t \u0111\u1ea1i d\u1ecbch c\u1ee7a s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n v\xe0 \u0111\u01a1n \u0111\u1ed9c.\\"\\n\\nD\xf9 sao c\xe2u n\xf3i \\"t\xf4i s\u1ebd ch\u1ebft m\u1ed9t m\xecnh\\" l\xe0 c\xe2u ph\xe0n n\xe0n ph\u1ed5 bi\u1ebfn v\u1edbi m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi. Trong gi\u1edbi khoa h\u1ecdc, n\xf3 s\xe1t h\u01a1n v\u1edbi c\xe2u n\xf3i \\"t\xf4i s\u1ebd ch\u1ebft *n\u1ebfu* t\xf4i \u0111\u01a1n \u0111\u1ed9c.\\"\\n\\nH\u1ec7 th\u1ed1ng mi\u1ec5n d\u1ecbch c\u1ee7a con ngu\u1eddi c\xf3 th\u1ec3 b\u1ecb \u1ea3nh hu\u1edfng do thi\u1ebfu tu\u01a1ng t\xe1c x\xe3 giao, v\xec v\u1eady nh\u1eefng con ngu\u1eddi \u0111\u01a1n \u0111\u1ed9c c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u kh\u1ea3 n\u0103ng ch\u1ebft s\u1edbm. S\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\xf2n nguy hi\u1ec3m h\u01a1n c\u1ea3 b\xe9o ph\xec v\xe0 nguy hi\u1ec3m b\u1eb1ng vi\u1ec7c h\xfat thu\u1ed1c. M\u1ed1i nguy h\u1ea1i n\xe0y \u0111u\u1ee3c coi l\xe0 nghi\xeam tr\u1ecdng \u0111\u1ebfn n\u1ed7i England \u0111\xe3 t\u1ea1o m\u1ed9t chi\u1ebfn d\u1ecbch \u0111\u1ec3 gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n.Bu\u1ed3n thay, s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n ch\u1ec9 d\u1eabn \u0111\u1ebfn s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n nhi\u1ec1u h\u01a1n. N\xe3o c\u1ee7a ngu\u1eddi c\xf3 \xedt tu\u01a1ng t\xe1c v\u1edbi ngu\u1eddi kh\xe1c th\u01b0\u1eddng ngh\u0129 con ng\u01b0\u1eddi l\xe0 m\u1ed9t m\u1ed1i hi\u1ec3m ho\u1ea1 v\xe0 c\xe0ng khi\u1ebfn ngu\u1eddi \u0111\xf3 kh\xf3 th\xe2n v\u1edbi ngu\u1eddi kh\xe1c.\u0110\u1ec3 hi\u1ec3u th\xeam v\u1ec1 v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 nan gi\u1ea3i n\xe0y, v\xe0 l\xe0m sao \u0111\u1ec3 gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft n\xf3, t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 n\xf3i chuy\u1ec7n v\u1edbi John Cacioppo, nh\xe0 t\xe2m l\xed h\u1ecdc t\u1ea1i \u0111\u1ea1i h\u1ecdc Chicago, ngu\u1eddi \u0111\xe3 vi\u1ebft s\xe1ch v\u1ec1 n\u1ed7i c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n v\xe0 \u0111\xe3 nghi\xean c\u1ee9u v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 n\xe0y chuy\xean s\xe2u. Du\u1edbi \u0111\xe2y l\xe0 b\u1ea3n ghi ch\xe9p cu\u1ed9c n\xf3i chuy\u1ec7n c\u1ee7a ch\xfang t\xf4i.\\n\\n---\\n\\n***Olga Khazan (O.K)***: Con ngu\u1eddi c\xf3 \u0111ang tr\u1edf n\xean \u0111\u01a1n \u0111\u1ed9c h\u01a1n kh\xf4ng th\u01b0a \xf4ng? N\u1ebfu \u0111\xfang th\xec \u0111\xe2u l\xe0 l\xed do?\\n\\n***John Cacioppo (J.C)***: Khi b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ecdc c\xe1c t\xe0i li\u1ec7u nghi\xean c\u1ee9u, b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd th\u1ea5y t\u1ec9 l\u1ec7 nh\u1eefng ngu\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n r\u01a1i v\xe0o 25 t\u1edbi 48 ph\u1ea7n tr\u0103m. T\xf4i th\u1ea5y London c\xf3 khuy\u1ebfn c\xe1o t\u1eb1ng 50 ph\u1ea7n tr\u0103m ngu\u1eddi London c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n, nh\u01b0ng d\u1eef li\u1ec7u n\xe0y kh\xf4ng chuy\xean s\xe2u n\xean \u0111\u1eebng qu\xe1 tin v\xe0o n\xf3. D\u1eef li\u1ec7u nghi\xean c\u1ee9u chuy\xean s\xe2u nh\u1ea5t n\u1eb1m trong nghi\xean c\u1ee9u s\u1ee9c kho\u1ebb v\xe0 ngh\u1ec9 h\u01b0u t\u1ea1i M\u1ef9. Nghi\xean c\u1ee9u n\xe0y \u0111u\u1ee3c h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 b\u1edfi ch\xednh ph\u1ee7 qua nhi\u1ec1u th\u1eadp k\u1ef7 v\xe0 \u0111\xf3 ch\xednh l\xe0 n\u01a1i t\xf4i d\u1ef1a v\xe0o \u0111\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0a ra c\xe1c nh\u1eadn \u0111\u1ecbnh. Khi ch\xfang ta nh\xecn v\xe0o c\xe1c b\u1ea3n th\u0103m d\xf2, t\u1ec9 l\u1ec7 c\u1ee7a s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n l\xe0 27, 28 ph\u1ea7n tr\u0103m. C\xe1c nh\u1eadn \u0111\u1ecbnh kh\u1ea3 thi nh\u1ea5t \u0111\u1ec1u d\u1ef1a v\xe0o n\xf3, t\u1ee9c t\u1ec9 l\u1ec7 n\xe0y \u0111\xe3 t\u0103ng t\u1eeb 3 \u0111\u1ebfn 7 ph\u1ea7n tr\u0103m trong v\xf2ng 20 n\u0103m qua.\\n\\n***O.K***: T\u1ec9 \u0111\xf3 kh\xf4ng h\u1ec1 cao, nh\u01b0ng li\u1ec7u c\xf3 l\u1eddi gi\u1ea3i th\xedch cho n\xf3? C\xf3 th\u1ec3 do m\u1ecdi ngu\u1eddi \u0111ang gi\xe0 ho\xe1 v\xe0 ngu\u1eddi gi\xe0 thu\u1eddng s\u1ed1ng m\u1ed9t m\xecnh?\\n\\n***J.C***: \u0110\u1ea7u ti\xean, \u0111\u1ec3 t\xf4i n\xf3i \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y. S\u1ed1ng m\u1ed9t m\xecnh, \u1edf m\u1ed9t m\xecnh v\xe0 v\xf2ng tr\xf2n c\xe1c m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ec1u c\xf3 \xedt s\u1ef1 li\xean quan. H\xe3y ngh\u0129 v\u1ec1 b\u1ec7nh nh\xe2n trong b\u1ec7nh vi\u1ec7n: \xa0h\u1ecd c\xf3 ng\u01b0\u1eddi xung quanh, h\u1ecd \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c quan t\xe2m v\xe0 gi\xfap \u0111\u1ee1 nh\u01b0ng h\u1ecd l\u1ea1i c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. \\"C\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n\\" (\u1edf quanh m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi nh\u01b0ng t\u1ef1 c\xf4 l\u1eadp m\xecnh) v\xe0 \\"c\xf4 \u0111\u1ed9c\\" (\u1edf m\u1ed9t m\xecnh) l\xe0 hai kh\xe1i ni\u1ec7m kh\xe1c nhau. Nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi ch\u1ed3ng ng\u01b0\u1eddi v\u1ee3 th\u01b0\u1eddng c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y \u0111\u1ee1 c\xf4 \u0111\u1ed9c h\u01a1n ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u0111ang \u0111\u1ed9c th\xe2n. Nh\u01b0ng h\u1ecd l\u1ea1i c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n khi h\u1ecd b\u1ecb xa l\xe1nh b\u1edfi h\u1ecd h\xe0ng v\xe0 gia \u0111\xecnh. C\xe1c y\u1ebfu t\u1ed1 \u0111\u1ec1u c\xf3 \xedt s\u1ef1 li\xean quan n\xean ch\xfang ta ph\u1ea3i \u0111\xe1nh gi\xe1 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n v\u1ec1 m\u1eb7t tinh th\u1ea7n ho\u1eb7c v\u1ec1 m\u1eb7t th\u1ec3 ch\u1ea5t.\\n\\n\u1ede lo\xe0i v\u1eadt, khi t\xe1ch m\u1ed9t con kh\u1ec9 v\xe0 b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ed3ng h\xe0nh c\u1ee7a n\xf3 th\xec ch\xfang ta th\u1ea5y x\u1ea3y ra hi\u1ec7n t\u01b0\u1ee3ng t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 \u1edf lo\xe0i ng\u01b0\u1eddi: ch\xfang c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n.\\n\\n***O.K***: T\u1ea1i sao ch\xfang ta th\u1ea5y s\u1ef1 gia t\u0103ng c\u1ee7a c\u01a1n d\u1ecbch mang t\xean \\"c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n\\"?\\n\\n***J.C***: C\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u y\u1ebfu t\u1ed1 v\u1ec1 v\u0103n h\xf3a v\xe0 m\xf4i tr\u01b0\u1eddng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 x\u1ea3y ra hi\u1ec7n t\u01b0\u1ee3ng n\xe0y. V\xed d\u1ee5: s\u1ef1 xu\u1ea5t hi\u1ec7n c\u1ee7a Internet gi\xfap con ng\u01b0\u1eddi k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi nhau nhi\u1ec1u h\u01a1n. Nh\u01b0ng n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n c\u1ee9 ch\u0103m ch\xfa \u0111\u1ecdc tin nh\u1eafn v\xe0 email trong l\xfac h\u1ecdp m\u1eb7t gia \u0111\xecnh th\xec \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 c\u0169ng kh\xf4ng h\u1eb3n l\xe0 \u0111\xfang.\\n\\nN\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n t\u1eadn d\u1ee5ng s\u1ef1 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i c\u1ee7a Internet nh\u01b0 m\u1ed9t n\u01a1i \u0111\u1ec3 g\u1eb7p g\u1ee1 - gi\u1edbi tr\u1ebb th\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0m \u0111i\u1ec1n n\xe0y; ch\xfang d\xf9ng Facebook \u0111\u1ec3 h\u1eb9n t\u1ea1i m\u1ed9t \u0111\u1ecba \u0111i\u1ec3m n\xe0o \u0111\xf3. \u0110i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 li\xean giao v\u1edbi s\u1ef1 thuy\xean gi\u1ea3m c\u1ee7a c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. N\u1ebfu s\u1ef1 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i c\u1ee7a Internet \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c d\xf9ng nh\u01b0 m\u1ed9t \u0111\xedch \u0111\u1ebfn [m\u1ed9t gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p] - v\xe0 tr\u1edb tr\xeau thay, nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n th\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0m \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y, h\u1ecd th\u01b0\u1eddng t\u1ef1 r\xfat m\xecnh v\xec t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\xe1c v\u1edbi ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c c\u1ea3m gi\xe1c nh\u01b0 m\u1ed9t s\u1ef1 tr\u1eebng ph\u1ea1t, v\xe0 c\xf3 l\u1ebd t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\xe1c online d\u01b0\u1edbi m\u1ed9t danh t\xednh gi\u1ea3, l\xe0m h\u1ecd c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y h\xf2a \u0111\u1ed3ng h\u01a1n. Nh\u01b0ng \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 kh\xf4ng l\xe0m h\u1ecd c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y b\u1edbt c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n.\\n\\nN\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n ch\u1ec9 c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y t\u1ef1 tin v\u1edbi b\u1ea3n th\xe2n qua m\u1ed9t danh t\xednh \u1ea3o tr\xean m\u1ea1ng th\xec \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 kh\xf4ng gi\xfap b\u1ea1n h\xf2a \u0111\u1ed3ng h\u01a1n. Nh\u01b0ng n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n nh\xecn v\u1ec1 kh\xeda c\u1ea1nh h\u1eb9n h\xf2 qua m\u1ea1ng \u1ea3o n\u01a1i b\u1ea1n g\u1eb7p g\u1ee1 m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi n\xean b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y b\u1edbt c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n.\\n\\n***O.K***: T\u1ea1i sao nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u1ed9c th\u01b0\u1eddng ngh\u0129 ti\u1ec7u c\u1ef1c trong c\xe1c m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 v\u1edbi ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c?\\n\\n***J.C***: C\xf3 hai h\u01b0\u1edbng \u0111\u1ec3 nh\xecn nh\u1eadn. C\xe1c th\u1ee9 nh\u1ea5t l\xe0 nh\u1eefng s\u1ef1 ki\u1ec7n ghi l\u1ea1i t\u1ea1i ph\u1ea7n ti\u1ec1m th\u1ee9c v\xe0 ph\u1ea7n c\xf2n l\u1ea1i t\u1ea1i ph\u1ea7n \xfd th\u1ee9c. V\xed d\u1ee5, khi b\u1ea1n \u0111\xf3i, b\u1ea1n c\u1ea3m nh\u1eadn \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c n\xf3 v\xe0 b\u1ea1n mu\u1ed1n \u0103n. M\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch c\u1ee7a c\u1ea3m gi\xe1c \u0111\xf3 th\xfac \u0111\u1ea9y b\u1ea1n \u0111i t\xecm \u0111\u1ed3 \u0103n tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi b\u1ea1n ki\u1ec7t s\u1ee9c v\xe0 kh\xf4ng c\xf2n n\u0103ng l\u01b0\u1ee3ng \u0111\u1ec3 \u0103n.\\n\\nV\xe0 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n th\xfac \u0111\u1ea9y b\u1ea1n s\u1eeda ch\u1eefa nh\u1eefng m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 \u0111\u1ea1ng phai nh\u1ea1t d\u1ea7n. V\xec v\u1eady m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi t\u1eadp trung v\xe0o c\xe1c m\u1ed1i tin quan tr\u1ecdng trong \u0111\u1eddi s\u1ed1ng \u0111\u1ec3 h\u1ecd c\xf3 th\u1ec3 h\xe0n g\u1eafn c\xe1c m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 \u0111\xf3.\\n\\nTrong l\xfac b\u1ea1n \u0111\xf3i, b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd tr\u1edf n\xean nh\u1ea1y c\u1ea3m h\u01a1n tr\u01b0\u1edbc v\u1ecb \u0111\u1eafng. L\xfd do l\xe0 v\xec trong qu\xe1 tr\xecnh ti\u1ebfn h\xf3a, v\u1ecb \u0111\u1eafng th\u01b0\u1eddng g\u1eafn li\u1ec1n v\u1edbi n\u1ecdc \u0111\u1ed9c. T\u1ee9c l\xe0 khi b\u1ea1n \u0111\xf3i, b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng \u0103n \u0111\u1ed3 \u0103n \u0111\u1eafng cho d\xf9 b\u1ea1n \u0111ang c\u1ed1 t\xecm \u0111\u1ed3 \u0103n \u0111\u1ec3 sinh t\u1ed3n.\\n\\nT\u01b0\u01a1ng t\u1ef1 v\u1edbi s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. N\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n nh\xecn v\u1ec1 lo\xe0i ng\u01b0\u1eddi t\u1ed1i c\u1ed5, h\u1ecd kh\xf4ng c\xf3 \u0111\u1ed1i x\u1eed t\u1ed1t \u0111\u1eb9p v\u1edbi nhau. Ch\xfang ta l\u1ee3i d\u1ee5ng nhau, ch\xfang ta tr\u1eebng ph\u1ea1t nhau, ch\xfang ta \u0111e d\u1ecda nhau, ch\xfang ta \xe9p bu\u1ed9c nhau. V\xe0 v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i l\xe0 t\xf4i mu\u1ed1n l\xe0m b\u1ea1n v\u1edbi ai m\xe0 l\xe0 t\xf4i c\u1ea7n ph\u1ea3i ph\xe2n bi\u1ec7t \u0111\xe2u l\xe0 b\u1ea1n, \u0111\xe2u l\xe0 k\u1ebb th\xf9. Nh\u01b0 v\u1ecb \u0111\u1eafng v\xe0 ng\u1ecdt, n\u1ecdc \u0111\u1ed9c v\xe0 kh\xf4ng \u0111\u1ed9c, n\u1ebfu t\xf4i ph\u1ea1m m\u1ed9t sai l\u1ea7m v\xe0 nh\u1eadn ra m\u1ed9t ng\u01b0\u1eddi t\u01b0\u1edfng l\xe0 k\u1ebb th\xf9 nh\u01b0ng th\u1ef1c ra l\xe0 b\u1ea1n th\xec kh\xf4ng sao, t\xf4i kh\xf4ng k\u1ebft b\u1ea1n nhanh nh\u01b0ng t\xf4i \u0111\xe3 s\u1ed1ng s\xf3t.\\n\\nNh\u01b0ng n\u1ebfu t\xf4i t\u01b0\u1edfng l\u1ea7m m\u1ed9t k\u1ebb th\xf9 l\xe0 b\u1ea1n th\xec t\xf4i s\u1ebd tr\u1ea3 gi\xe1 b\u1eb1ng m\u1ea1ng s\u1ed1ng c\u1ee7a t\xf4i. Qua qu\xe1 tr\xecnh ti\u1ebfn h\xf3a, ch\xfang ta ti\u1ebfn h\xf3a \u0111\u1ec3 nh\u1eadn bi\u1ebft \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u tr\xean.\\n\\nV\xe0 \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 t\u1ea1o n\xean nh\u1eefng mong ch\u1edd, v\xec t\xf4i th\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111o\xe1n tr\u01b0\u1edbc l\xe0 nh\u1eefng th\u1ee9 t\xf4i s\u1ebd th\u1ea5y. N\u1ebfu t\xf4i ngh\u0129 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd tr\u1edf n\xean th\xf9 d\u1ecbch th\xec t\xf4i s\u1ebd n\xf3i nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u r\u1ea5t kh\xe1c so v\u1edbi nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u khi t\xf4i tin b\u1ea1n h\u01a1n.\\n\\nB\u1ea1n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c th\xfac \u0111\u1ea9y \u0111\u1ec3 h\xe0n g\u1eafn. Nh\u01b0ng nh\u1eefng m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 kh\xf4ng r\xf5 r\xe0ng (promiscuous connection) c\xf3 th\u1ec3 d\u1eabn t\u1edbi c\xe1i ch\u1ebft. M\u1ed9t c\u01a1 ch\u1ebf trong h\u1ec7 th\u1ea7n kinh ph\xe1t t\xe1c \u0111\u1ec3 b\u1ea1n tr\u1edf n\xean nghi ng\u1edd h\u01a1n tr\u01b0\u1edbc khi k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\u1edbi ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c.\\n\\n***O.K***: M\u1ed9t s\u1ed1 h\u1ecdc thuy\u1ebft cho r\u1eb1ng khi ta t\u1ea1o ra nhi\u1ec1u c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i \u0111\u1ec3 x\xe3 giao h\u01a1n, k\u1ec3 c\u1ea3 c\u1ea3 thi\u1ec7n k\u1ef9 n\u0103ng giao ti\u1ebfp kh\xf4ng h\u1ec1 gi\u1ea3m s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. V\xec sao l\u1ea1i c\xf3 hi\u1ec7n t\u01b0\u1ee3ng nh\u01b0 tr\xean?\\n\\n***J.C***: T\u01b0\u01a1ng t\xe1c x\xe3 giao (social interaction) c\xf2n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c g\u1ecdi l\xe0 s\u1ef1 giao ti\u1ebfp (social engagement), t\u1ee9c l\xe0 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c ch\u1eefa kh\u1ecfi nh\u1edd g\u1eb7p g\u1ee1 v\u1edbi m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi. N\u1ebfu h\u1ecd kh\xf4ng c\xf4 \u0111\u1ed9c th\xec h\u1ecd s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. C\xe1c tr\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u1ea1i h\u1ecdc th\u01b0\u1eddng ngh\u0129 nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0y v\xe0 \u0111\xf3 l\xe0 l\xfd do t\u1ea1i sao tr\u01b0\u1eddng th\u01b0\u1eddng t\u1ed5 ch\u1ee9c c\xe1c s\u1ef1 ki\u1ec7n \u0111\u1ec3 giao l\u01b0u. B\u1ea1n nh\u1edb nh\u1eefng s\u1ef1 ki\u1ec7n \u0111\xf3 ch\u1ee9? Ch\xfang th\u01b0\u1eddng kh\xf4ng th\xe0nh c\xf4ng.\\n\\n\u1ede b\xean c\u1ea1nh ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c kh\xf4ng c\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y g\u1ea7n g\u0169i, v\xe0 t\xecnh tr\u1ea1ng l\u1ebb loi kh\xf4ng c\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 b\u1ea1n c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. B\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\u1ea3 hai \u0111i\u1ec1u tr\xean, nh\u01b0ng th\u01b0\u1eddng ch\xfang ta hay t\xe1ch m\xecnh kh\u1ecfi \u0111\xe1m \u0111\xf4ng.\\n\\nM\u1ed9t ng\u01b0\u1eddi m\u1eb9 tr\u1ebb th\u01b0\u1eddng ch\u0103m s\xf3c ng\u01b0\u1eddi con t\u1eadn t\xecnh, nh\u01b0ng \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 kh\xf4ng c\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 \xf4ng ch\u1ed3ng ph\u1ea3i \xe9p c\xf4 \u1ea5y l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c \u0111\xf3 24/7. Anh ta c\xf3 th\u1ec3 t\u1ea1o cho co v\u1ee3 m\u1ed9t kh\xf4ng gian ri\xeang \u0111\u1ec3 th\u01b0 gi\xe3n v\xe0 ti\u1ebfp s\u1ee9c c\xf4 \u1ea5y \u0111\u1ec3 ch\u0103m s\xf3c ng\u01b0\u1eddi con t\u1ed1t h\u01a1n. Kh\xf4ng gian ri\xeang \u1ea5y gia t\u0103ng s\u1ef1 k\u1ebft n\u1ed1i v\xe0 giao l\u01b0u ch\u1ee9 n\xf3 kh\xf4ng h\u1ec1 ng\u0103n c\u1ea3n vi\u1ec7c \u0111\xf3.\\n\\n***O.K***: C\xf3 nh\u1eefng ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n n\xe0o?\\n\\n***J.C***: C\xf3 s\u1ef1 h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 cho ng\u01b0\u1eddi gi\xe0 c\xf4 \u0111\u1ed9c. Nh\u1eefng ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh \u0111\xf3 gi\xfap h\u1ecd g\u1eb7p g\u1ee1 m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi v\xe0 c\xf3 \u0111\u1ed3 \u0103n th\u1ee9c u\u1ed1ng m\u1ed7i th\xe1ng. B\u1eb1ng nh\u1eefng s\u1ef1 h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 n\xe0y, ch\xfang s\u1ebd gi\xfap ng\u01b0\u1eddi gi\xe0 r\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u do n\u1ed7i s\u1ee3 l\u1edbn nh\u1ea5t c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi gi\xe0 l\xe0 ch\u1ebft m\xe0 kh\xf4ng ai bi\u1ebft. B\u1eb1ng nh\u1eefng ch\u01b0\u01a1ng tr\xecnh nh\u01b0 tr\xean, h\u1ecd c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y an \u1ee7i h\u01a1n.\\n\\nTuy nhi\xean s\u1ef1 h\u1ed7 tr\u1ee3 n\xe0y ch\u1ec9 gi\u1ea3i \u0111\xe1p m\u1ed9t ph\u1ea7n n\xe0o n\u1ed7i bu\u1ed3n c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi gi\xe0. N\xf3 ch\u1ec9 l\xe0m v\u01a1i \u0111i c\xe1i \xfd ngh\u0129 s\u1ed1ng ch\u1ebft kh\xf4ng m\u1ed9t ai hay.\\n\\n***O.K***: \xd4ng s\u1ebd c\xf3 nh\u1eefng li\u1ec7u ph\xe1p g\xec cho nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u1ed9c nh\u01b0ng kh\xf4ng mu\u1ed1n giao ti\u1ebfp v\u1edbi ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c?\\n\\n***J.C***: Nh\u1eefng g\xec ch\xfang t\xf4i d\u1ea1y l\xe0 m\u1ed9t b\u1ed9 k\u1ef9 n\u0103ng bao g\u1ed3m: c\xe1c \u0111\u1ecdc \xfd ngh\u0129 c\u1ee7a ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c qua n\xe9t m\u1eb7t v\xe0 c\u1eed ch\u1ec9 c\u1ee7a h\u1ecd, v\xe0 ch\u1ec9 ra nh\u1eefng sai l\u1ea7m trong c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ecdc ra sao. C\xf3 nh\u1eefng c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ecdc suy ngh\u0129 \u0111\xfang v\xe0 c\xf3 nhi\u1ec1u c\xe1ch \u0111\u1ecdc sai v\xe0 ch\xfang t\xf4i s\u1ebd kh\u1eafc ph\u1ee5c ch\xfang.\\n\\nV\u1eady khi n\xe0o b\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 \u0111\u1eb7t ni\u1ec1m tin v\xe0o ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c? B\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0 m\u1ed9t con ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\u1edfi m\u1edf nh\u01b0ng b\u1ea1n ph\u1ea3i th\u1eadt d\xe8 ch\u1eebng v\xe0 lu\xf4n c\u1ea3nh gi\xe1c. B\u1ea1n c\xf3 nh\u1eefng l\xfd thuy\u1ebft kh\xe1c nhau trong m\u1ed9t t\xecnh hu\u1ed1ng \u0111\u1ec3 th\u1eed. V\xed d\u1ee5, b\u1ea1n t\u1edbi m\u1ed9t b\u1eefa ti\u1ec7c, b\u1ea1n n\xf3i chuy\u1ec7n v\u1edbi nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi v\xe0 b\u1ea1n th\u1eed cho h\u1ecd m\u1ed9t c\u01a1 h\u1ed9i.\\n\\nNh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u kh\xe1c ch\xfang t\xf4i nh\u1eadn th\u1ea5y l\xe0 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\xf3 li\xean quan t\u1edbi c\xe1i \\"t\xf4i\\". Khi b\u1ea1n t\u1eadp trung v\xe0o nh\u1eefng h\u1eadu qu\u1ea3 nhi\u1ec1u h\u01a1n l\xfac b\xecnh th\u01b0\u1eddng trong l\xfac b\u1ea1n c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n th\xec b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd thu h\u1eb9p m\xecnh h\u01a1n. \u0110\xf4i l\xfac b\u1ea1n n\xf3i chuy\u1ec7n v\u1edbi m\u1ed9t ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n, h\u1ecd s\u1ebd n\xf3i kh\xf4ng ng\u1eebng v\xe0 b\u1ea1n kh\xf4ng th\u1ec3 tr\u1ed1n \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c. V\u1eady b\u1ea1n ph\u1ea3i giao ti\u1ebfp nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o \u0111\u1ec3 tr\xe1nh lan man? B\u1ea1n ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u1ec3 \xfd t\u1edbi s\u1ef1 t\u01b0\u01a1ng t\xe1c v\xe0 h\xf2a h\u1ee3p c\u1ee7a c\u1ea3 hai b\xean tr\xf2 chuy\u1ec7n ch\u1ee9 kh\xf4ng ch\u1ec9 m\xecnh b\u1ea1n.\\n\\n***O.K***: \xd4ng c\xf3 l\u1eddi khuy\xean n\xe0o cho nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n?\\n\\n***J.C***: M\u1ed9t trong nh\u1eefng hi\u1ec3u l\u1ea7m khi n\xf3i v\u1ec1 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n l\xe0 \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a c\u1ee7a s\u1ef1 \\"c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n\\". M\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi th\u01b0\u1eddng ngh\u0129 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n l\xe0 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 l\u1eadp c\u1ee7a b\u1ea3n th\xe2n v\xe0 \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a \u1ea5y d\u1eabn t\u1edbi nh\u1eefng gi\u1ea3i ph\xe1p kh\xf4ng tri\u1ec7t \u0111\u1ec3. V\xe0 n\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n c\xf3 \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a theo h\u01b0\u1edbng \u0111\xf3, b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd ngh\u0129: \\"ch\xe0, m\xecnh s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng bao gi\u1edd tho\xe1t kh\u1ecfi v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 n\xe0y, m\xecnh th\u1eadt v\xf4 d\u1ee5ng.\\" V\xe0 l\xfac \u0111\xf3 b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd kh\xe9p m\xecnh h\u01a1n.\\n\\nM\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch c\u1ee7a s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n t\u1ef1a nh\u01b0 m\u1ee5c \u0111\xedch c\u1ee7a c\u1ea3m gi\xe1c \u0111\xf3i. C\u01a1n \u0111\xf3i \u1ea3nh h\u01b0\u1edfng c\u01a1 th\u1ec3 v\u1eadt ch\u1ea5t. C\xf2n c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n th\xec \u1ea3nh h\u01b0\u1edfng t\u1edbi m\u1eb7t t\xe2m h\u1ed3n b\xean trong c\u01a1 th\u1ec3. B\u1ea1n c\u1ea7n c\u1ea3 hai \u0111\u1ec3 t\u1ed3n t\u1ea1i v\xe0 s\u1ed1ng h\u1ea1nh ph\xfac. Ch\xfang ta l\xe0 lo\xe0i v\u1eadt th\xedch giao ti\u1ebfp.\\n\\nKh\xe1i ni\u1ec7m c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n m\xe0 m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi th\u01b0\u1eddng bi\u1ebft \u0111\u1ebfn ch\u1ec9 k\u1ec3 \u0111\u1ebfn s\u1ef1 c\xf4 l\u1eadp b\u1ea3n th\xe2n kh\u1ecfi m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi v\xe0 \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a \u0111\xf3 kh\xf4ng h\u1eb3n l\xe0 \u0111\xfang. M\u1eb7t kh\xe1c c\u1ee7a \u0111\u1ecbnh ngh\u0129a c\u1ee7a c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n l\xe0 v\u1ec1 s\u1ef1 gi\xfap \u0111\u1ee1 t\u1eeb ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c. Nh\u01b0ng ch\xfang \xa0c\u0169ng kh\xf4ng gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft tri\u1ec7t \u0111\u1ec3 v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 v\xec s\u1ef1 gi\xfap \u0111\u1ee1 ph\u1ea3i \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c h\u1ed3i \u0111\xe1p c\u1ea3 b\xean ng\u01b0\u1eddi g\u1eedi v\xe0 b\xean ng\u01b0\u1eddi nh\u1eadn. Ch\u1ec9 nh\u1eadn s\u1ef1 gi\xfap \u0111\u1ee1 t\u1eeb ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng l\xe0m v\u01a1i \u0111i n\u1ed7i bu\u1ed3n. Khi ch\xfang ta gi\xfap \u0111\u1ee1 ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xe1c, ch\xfang ta s\u1ebd th\u01b0\u1eddng c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y t\u1ef1 h\xe0o v\u1ec1 b\u1ea3n th\xe2n h\u01a1n. Gi\u1ea3 s\u1eed b\u1ea1n l\xe0m vi\u1ec7c \u1edf m\u1ed9t c\u0103n b\u1ebfp nh\u1ecf, v\xe0 b\u1ea1n ch\u1ee3t th\u1ea5y m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi \u0111\u1ec1u t\u1ed1t b\u1ee5ng , th\xec h\u1ecd \u0111ang ph\u1ea3n \u1ee9ng t\xedch c\u1ef1c cho nh\u1eefng vi\u1ec7c b\u1ea1n \u0111\xe3 l\xe0m cho h\u1ecd.\\n\\nM\u1ed9t hi\u1ec3u l\u1ea7m kh\xe1c v\u1ec1 s\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n l\xe0 nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi thi\u1ebfu k\u1ef9 n\u0103ng giao ti\u1ebfp th\u01b0\u1eddng l\xe0 nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. V\xe0 b\u1ea1n bi\u1ebft kh\xf4ng? \u0110\xf3 kh\xf4ng h\u1eb3n l\xe0 \u0111\xfang. N\u1ebfu b\u1ea1n giao ti\u1ebfp si\xeau t\u1ec7 th\xec b\u1ea1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n h\u01a1n, ok. Nh\u01b0ng nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n th\u01b0\u1eddng c\xf3 th\u1ec3 giao ti\u1ebfp r\u1ea5t b\xecnh th\u01b0\u1eddng. Nh\xe0 tri\u1ec7u ph\xfa, t\u1ef7 ph\xfa th\u01b0\u1eddng c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. R\u1ea5t nhi\u1ec1u c\xe1c v\u1eadn \u0111\u1ed9ng vi\xean c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n. Nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi mu\u1ed1n k\u1ebft b\u1ea1n v\u1edbi nhi\u1ec1u ng\u01b0\u1eddi [c\u0169ng c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n], nh\u01b0ng b\u1ea1n s\u1ebd c\u1ea3m th\u1ea5y th\u1ebf n\xe0o khi b\u1ea1n ngh\u0129 nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi mu\u1ed1n k\u1ebft b\u1ea1n v\u1edbi b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ec1u mu\u1ed1n l\u1ee3i d\u1ee5ng \u0111\u1ecba v\u1ecb, danh th\u1ebf c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n?\\n\\n\u0110\xe2y l\xe0 l\xfd do t\u1ea1i sao b\u1ea1n th\u1ea5y nh\u1eefng v\u1eadn \u0111\u1ed9ng vi\xean n\u1ed5i ti\u1ebfng \u0111\u1ebfn t\u1eeb khu d\xe2n c\u01b0 ngh\xe8o v\u1eabn gi\u1eef nh\u1eefng m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 c\u0169, k\u1ec3 c\u1ea3 khi h\u1ecd kh\xf4ng mang l\u1ea1i l\u1ee3i \xedch g\xec. Nh\u1eefng m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 \u0111\xf3 th\u01b0\u1eddng \u0111\u01b0\u1ee3c coi l\xe0 ch\xe2n th\u1eadt h\u01a1n.\\n\\n***O.K***: Nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\xf3 th\u1ec3 l\xe0m g\xec \u0111\u1ec3 tr\xe1nh kh\u1ecfi v\u1ea5n \u0111\u1ec1 n\xe0y?\\n\\n***J.C***: \u0110i l\xe0m t\xecnh nguy\u1ec7n v\xe0o l\u0129nh v\u1ef1c \xeau th\xedch c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n. T\xf4i \u0111\xe3 s\xe1ng l\u1eadp ra t\u1eeb vi\u1ebft t\u1eaft \\"EASE\\" - d\u1ea7n d\u1ea7n h\xe0n g\u1eafn l\u1ea1i (ease your way back) nh\u1eefng m\u1ed1i quan h\u1ec7 c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n. Ch\u1eef E \u0111\u1ea7u ti\xean c\xf3 ngh\u0129a l\xe0 \\"extend yourself\\" - th\u1ea3 l\u1ecfng, n\u1edbi r\u1ed9ng b\u1ea3n th\xe2n (khi giao ti\u1ebfp). Nh\u01b0ng n\xean th\u1ea3 l\xf2ng t\u1eebng ch\xfat m\u1ed9t \u0111\u1ec3 gi\u1eef an to\xe0n cho b\u1ea1n.\\n\\nCh\u1eef A ngh\u0129a l\xe0 \\"have an action plan\\" - c\xf3 m\u1ed9t k\u1ebf ho\u1ea1ch gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft. Gi\u1ea3i quy\u1ebft n\u1ed7i c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n l\xe0 \u0111i\u1ec1u kh\xf4ng d\u1ec5 d\xe0ng. M\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi kh\xf4ng nh\u1ea5t ph\u1ea3i th\xedch b\u1ea1n, v\xe0 \u0111a s\u1ed1 s\u1ebd kh\xf4ng \u01b0a b\u1ea1n. V\xe0 b\u1ea1n ph\u1ea3i ch\u1ea5p nh\u1eadn \u0111i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3, n\xf3 kh\xf4ng ph\u1ea3i l\xe0 s\u1ef1 ph\xe1n x\xe9t s\u1ed1 ph\u1eadn c\u1ee7a b\u1ea1n. H\u1ecfi th\u0103m m\u1ecdi ng\u01b0\u1eddi v\xe0 n\xf3i v\u1ec1 nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u h\u1ecd quan t\xe2m.\\n\\nCh\u1eef S ngh\u0129a l\xe0 \\"seek collectives\\". Con ng\u01b0\u1eddi th\xedch nh\u1eefng c\xe1 th\u1ec3 t\u01b0\u01a1ng \u0111\u1ed3ng v\u1edbi h\u1ecd, nh\u1eefng ng\u01b0\u1eddi chia s\u1ebb nh\u1eefng ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng, gi\xe1 tr\u1ecb chung nhau. \u0110i\u1ec1u \u0111\xf3 s\u1ebd gi\xfap hai b\xean \u0111\u1ebfn g\u1ea7n nhau h\u01a1n.\\n\\nV\xe0 cu\u1ed1i c\xf9ng l\xe0 khi tham gia c\xe1c ho\u1ea1t \u0111\u1ed9ng, \\"Expect\\" - mong ch\u1edd nh\u1eefng \u0111i\u1ec1u t\u1ed1t \u0111\u1eb9p nh\u1ea5t. V\xec \u0111i\u1ec1u n\xe0y s\u1ebd gi\xfap b\u1ea1n \u0111\u1ed1i m\u1eb7t v\u1edbi s\u1ef1 c\u1ea3nh gi\xe1c qu\xe1 \u0111\u1ed9 c\u1ee7a b\u1ea3n th\xe2n tr\u01b0\u1edbc m\u1ed1i nguy hi\u1ec3m mang t\xean \\"b\xe8 b\u1ea1n\\".\\n\\nNgu\u1ed3n: **[The Atlantic](https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2017/04/how-loneliness-begets-loneliness/521841/)**"},{"id":"why-i-switched-from-onenote-to-notion","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/why-i-switched-from-onenote-to-notion","editUrl":"https://github.com/fineon/fineon.github.io/tree/main/blog/Why I Switched from OneNote to Notion.md","source":"@site/blog/Why I Switched from OneNote to Notion.md","title":"Why I Switched from OneNote to Notion","description":"What is Notion?","date":"2021-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"September 14, 2021","tags":[{"label":"notion","permalink":"/blog/tags/notion"},{"label":"migration","permalink":"/blog/tags/migration"}],"readingTime":3.505,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Ian Nguyen","title":"Author","url":"https://github.com/fineon","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"why-i-switched-from-onenote-to-notion","title":"Why I Switched from OneNote to Notion","author":"Ian Nguyen","author_title":"Author","author_url":"https://github.com/fineon","author_image_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4","date":"2021-09-14T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["notion","migration"]},"prevItem":{"title":"S\u1ef1 c\xf4 \u0111\u01a1n c\u1ee9 ti\u1ebfp di\u1ec5n nh\u01b0 th\u1ebf n\xe0o?","permalink":"/blog/su-co-don-cu-tiep-dien-nhu-the-nao"},"nextItem":{"title":"The Lenovo Legion 5i Review","permalink":"/blog/lenovo-legion5i-review"}},"content":"## What is Notion?\\n\\nNotion is a simple notetaking/ productivity platform that is available on Windows, MacOS, iOS, Android and Web. Notion operates on the concept of [pages](https://www.notion.so/Create-a-new-page-6c3fe9aad94749099ea4bdfc072e5f97). Pages host all available contents and sub pages, including text and image-based content, [database tables](https://www.notion.so/Intro-to-databases-fd8cd2d212f74c50954c11086d85997e), different layout structures and many more. Notion offers a lot of flexibility when it comes to data display and data types, which can fit multitude of needs in different usage settings. For me, I needed a tool that is fast, responsive and can export to other common file formats like [Markdown](https://www.markdownguide.org/getting-started/). \\n\\n## Why Notion over OneNote?\\n\\nNotion has been supporting the features I have been looking for, such as: \\n\\n- **Markdown support**: This is the biggest feature that pulled me in. Since Markdown files can be parsed by different tools and widely supported, my content can be easily exported and imported between different platforms. I can also use Markdown syntax to quickly format my content as I type. My syntax and format in a Markdown file will be preserved and can be displayed on other platforms quickly.\\n- **Diverse layout**: Another neat feature in Notion is that you can insert different content/ data type in a page and organize them in your preferred layout. Notion supports multi-column layout and KanBan, which provides flexibility in content display. One Note pales in this aspect.\\n- **Common file export**: Notion can export all content in common file formats, like `.md` Markdown, `.html` HTML and `.pdf` PDF files. This is very useful for migration from one platform to another, such as from WordPress to a Markdown-based site generator. My old OneNote application was powerful anf functional, but it only allows `.one` file exports. `.one` file format is not universally recognized and cannot be easily parsed compared to `.md` Markdown files.\\n- **Fast and responsive web platform**: This is also another winning feature for me, as Notion\'s web platform is very simple to use and responsive to editing flow. All of my edits are saved instantly. OneNote, on the other hand, performs much slower on the web platform.\\n- **Growing community**: I actually heard about Notion from my university peers and company teams that often use Notion for collaboration. Notion\'s future looks bright as there are active communities looking for ways to use it to fit their productivity needs.\\n\\n## Notion Communities\\n\\nAs more people are discovering about Notion, many enthusiasts have been creating various contents to share Notion\'s best tips and tricks. \\n\\nThe productivity community has set its eyes on Youtube as its new home, which housed an abundant videos about how each person use Notion to boost their workflow. \\n\\n![Youtube search result displaying Notion tricks](./assets/Why-I-Switched-from-OneNote-to-Notion/Untitled.png)\\n\\nSource: [Youtube.com](https://youtube.com)\\n\\nThe \\"studyblr\\" community on Tumblr is also sharing various tips and Notion templates for any curious students looking to take note more efficiently. \\"Studyblr\\" is a niche community on Tumblr that promote productivity and study inspirations and tips. \\n\\n![Tumblr search result displaying Notion tips](./assets/Why-I-Switched-from-OneNote-to-Notion/Untitled1.png)\\n\\nSource: [Tumblr.com](https://tumblr.com)\\n\\n## Extending Past Notetaking\\n\\nThe *notion* of Notion as a pure notetaking platform is extending beyond its main functionality. \\n\\nIt can now act as a Content Management System (CMS) that supplies content and data to build a website. [Super](https://super.so) is a unique company that build websites based solely on Notion. Their service offer all-in-one website management and building with Notion. \\n\\n![Screenshot of Super homepage](./assets/Why-I-Switched-from-OneNote-to-Notion/Untitled2.png)\\n\\nSome examples: \\n\\n- A personal website: [https://redgregory.me](https://redgregory.me/)\\n- A knowledge base platform: [https://support.milliegiving.com](https://support.milliegiving.com/)\\n- A personal portfolio site: [https://anotioneer.com/aNotioneer-be59e14d857a4d658db394a0441a3b88](https://www.notion.so/aNotioneer-be59e14d857a4d658db394a0441a3b88)\\n\\nNotion pages can also report web analytics about who visited a Notion page, thanks to [Notionlytics](https://notionlytics.com/#steps-01-655321). \\n\\nI am amazed to see a productivity tool stretching above its general purpose to provide something new entirely.\\n\\n## Features to be Improved\\n\\nNotion is still evolving and developing as we speak, and it is no special target exempt from a few issues. As of Sept 14th, 2021, Notion\'s spell checker does not work very well in pages right now. There are no options to turn it on either. Apparently, pages need to have a lot of words before spell check is turned on, according to [Notion\'s tweet](https://twitter.com/NotionHQ/status/1164664802754453504?s=20). I have not seen this feature turned on for me yet, but I\'m sure it will be completed in future iterations."},{"id":"lenovo-legion5i-review","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/lenovo-legion5i-review","editUrl":"https://github.com/fineon/fineon.github.io/tree/main/blog/Legion-5i-Gen-6.md","source":"@site/blog/Legion-5i-Gen-6.md","title":"The Lenovo Legion 5i Review","description":"So far it has been working well! Everything is silky smooth and functional.","date":"2021-06-08T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"June 8, 2021","tags":[{"label":"laptop","permalink":"/blog/tags/laptop"},{"label":"review","permalink":"/blog/tags/review"}],"readingTime":1.535,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Ian Nguyen","title":"Author","url":"https://github.com/fineon","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"lenovo-legion5i-review","title":"The Lenovo Legion 5i Review","author":"Ian Nguyen","author_title":"Author","author_url":"https://github.com/fineon","author_image_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4","date":"2021-06-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["laptop","review"]},"prevItem":{"title":"Why I Switched from OneNote to Notion","permalink":"/blog/why-i-switched-from-onenote-to-notion"},"nextItem":{"title":"PUSH Festival, Art and Access Recap","permalink":"/blog/push-festival-art-and-access-recap"}},"content":"So far it has been working well! Everything is silky smooth and functional. \\n\\n:::tip Test Checklist\\nI\'d suggest checking out a few items that didn\'t really work propoerly on this legion 5i\\n- **Lenovo Vantage application**: always crashed upon opening. I had to reinstall it to get it working again. This issue is also documented on user support forum. Not sure what is causing it exactly. \\n:::\\n\\n## My Test Cases\\n\\n1. Booting up React dev server. Initial startup is so much faster than my older Dell. \\n2. Using multiple Chrome tabs (actually I use Vivaldi - a very customizable Chrome). It can handle over 20+ tabs just fine while my Dell already struggles with 5-10 tabs. \\n3. Destiny 2 gameplay. Gameplay is smooth and no jittering frames. \\n\\n## Pros\\n\\nSo far, everything is working fine and super fast! \\n\\n- Switching between multiple music video works faster compared to the sluggish speed on my Dell XPS 13.\\n- I can open multiple tabs on Vivaldi without experiencing delays or lags.\\n- Apps are super responsive upon sleeping and waking up. No more delays in interactions. \\n- Destiny 2 is booting up just fine. The gameplay is smooth as well. \\n\\n## Cons\\n\\nThat said, there are a few things I noticed while using the Legion 5i\\n\\n- Fan noise is super loud. No need to go to the airport when I\'ve got a mini airport simulation at home with kind of fan noise. \\n- Laptop heat. Extended GPU usage will make the laptop hotter than usual. But it can\'t beat the magma-heat from my old Dell laptop.\\n- The Lenovo Vantage  froze everytime it was opened. But i managed to fix it by reinstalling the app. \\n\\n\\nFor my initial tests and usage, the Lenovo Legion 5i is doing much better than my older Dell XPS 13 already :)"},{"id":"push-festival-art-and-access-recap","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/push-festival-art-and-access-recap","editUrl":"https://github.com/fineon/fineon.github.io/tree/main/blog/PUSH Festival, Art and Access Recap.md","source":"@site/blog/PUSH Festival, Art and Access Recap.md","title":"PUSH Festival, Art and Access Recap","description":"The PUSH festival held an interesting conversation on Friday, Jan. 25th, 2019.\xa0The event\xa0was an expansive panel of discussion about arts, theatre and where accessibility and the disability community fit in. Does the experience of art performers have to be separate from diversity and inclusion?","date":"2019-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","formattedDate":"January 15, 2019","tags":[{"label":"recap","permalink":"/blog/tags/recap"}],"readingTime":6.04,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Ian Nguyen","title":"Author","url":"https://github.com/fineon","imageURL":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"push-festival-art-and-access-recap","title":"PUSH Festival, Art and Access Recap","author":"Ian Nguyen","author_title":"Author","author_url":"https://github.com/fineon","author_image_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/38566281?v=4","date":"2019-01-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["recap"]},"prevItem":{"title":"The Lenovo Legion 5i Review","permalink":"/blog/lenovo-legion5i-review"}},"content":"*The [PUSH festival](https://pushfestival.ca) held an interesting conversation on Friday, Jan. 25th, 2019.\xa0[The event](https://pushfestival.ca/shows/festival-2019/critical-ideas-arts-access/)\xa0was an expansive panel of discussion about arts, theatre and where accessibility and the disability community fit in. Does the experience of art performers have to be separate from diversity and inclusion?*\\n\\n## The issue of \\"I feel sorry for you\\"\\n\\nThe first panel judge -\xa0**Dawn Jani Birley**\xa0spoke from her own experience as a third generation of deaf family. Her life motto is \\"Anything is possible in life\\". She felt contented with her life as she was in a rich culture and tightly-knit community.\\n\\nHowever, there were struggles in life that still hindered the talented art performer. Birley traced these issues to the lack of governmental support for deaf communities and the lack of support for deaf people in performance art department.\\n\\nIt was also the attitude of pitying on deaf people that challenged Burley\'s life journey. People would often think it is unfortunate for deaf people to live their own way.\\n\\n\\"My life is wonderful but your attitude is the struggle that we deal with\\", she said.\\n\\nBirley accepted deafness as part of her identity and her own way of life, although different from the social norm, had always been positive and exciting. The performer\xa0believed that arts were platforms for working towards understanding.\\n\\n## Creativity knows no bounds\\n\\nNext, came the turn for\xa0**Ravi Jain - Creative director**\\n\\nThe director started with his background and past work, which was theatre. It was a place for creativity. Jain believed that creativity can be inclusive, regardless of race and gender, which led to the concept of a culturally diverse theatre.\\n\\nJain was grateful for his past work with many actors with different backgrounds, who brought about a multi-colored lens of opinion.\\n\\nOn inclusion and diversity, the creative director believed that the more inclusive it was, the better the art.\\n\\nAdding to Jain\'s point, art performer Birley told her own example to explain that better support meant improved art performance. When she was working in Finland, Birley had a 24/7 interpreter provided by the Finish government. The constant flowing communication between Birley and the art director she was collaborating with facilitated strong team work ethic and final product improvements.\\n\\n## Pity is petty\\n\\nResonating on the Birley\'s experience as a deaf person,\xa0**Denise Read,**\xa0owner of ASLSQ Entertainment, emphasized the discrimination against deaf people is alarming.\\n\\nRead first experienced this when people told her pursuing art was not compatible to her personal background.\\n\\nThis didn\'t stop her from pursuing the dream. Read believed that the theater\xa0was just a way to express oneself and that it could always be inclusive.\\n\\nThe belief that being a deaf person meant they were worthless was problematic, Read said. The\xa0governments\'s\xa0reporting deaf people as \\"hearing impaired\\" meant they were something less than an able-bodied person. In fact, she much prefer the word \\"deaf\\" used to describe herself. Read claimed proudly that the deaf community is rich in both language and culture.\\n\\nShe also believed that being deaf doesn\'t mean disabled. It means diverse ability to her. She would like to see a play, where a main character is cast by deaf and blind actors. The inclusion of deaf people in art performances doesn\'t decrease the quality of it. In fact, it enhances it.\\n\\nOn ASL and sign languages, Read stressed that they play an important part in her life. In the past, she had heard peculiar questions from people around her, such as \\"Can you read lips?\\".\xa0 A deaf person doesn\'t always know how to read lips in order to communicate, they use ASL instead. For satire, Read just replied: \\"can you read my hands?\\"\\n\\nDelivering her last point, Read wants to see more collaboration with allies of minority communities and the immersion of deaf culture and language in mainstream society.\\n\\nWorking towards the goal of inclusion and arts, Read founded her own art company called ASLSQ entertainment as she believes art and theater are impactful and expressive in their nature, which would greatly enhances the lives of many people, regardless of race, gender or abilities.\\n\\n## The Utopia\\n\\nThe fourth speaker was\xa0**JD Derbyshire**, who is an ally. She started her speech with the vision of a Utopian, where human expressions is unhindered and diversity flourishes.\\n\\nNext, Derbyshire proposed a method to move forward towards her vision: education and role models. Although it takes time and money, education would greatly improve society\'s knowledge and sympathy towards minority groups. She added that there should be more involved process to accommodate deaf people.\\n\\nThe current challenge, according to Derbyshire, is the visibility of art and accessibility and the lack of support system to make her vision come true.\\n\\n## Intersectionality - the new diversity?\\n\\nBack to\xa0**Dawn Jani Birley**, the performer challenged the meaning of \\"diversity\\" and what it includes. For the most part, race and sexuality is often mentioned on the media, but not the deaf community.\\n\\nInstead, Birley would prefer the idea of \\"intersectionality\\". The concept would identify and include various minority groups and the support systems that match them, such as sign interpreters for deaf people. Although this seems like a more ideal concept, true inclusion is an ongoing work.\\n\\nDespite her critiques of diversity, Birley believes in it and the community she had built. She enjoys her work and the joy of leaning new language and culture.\\n\\n## Mismatched portrayal\\n\\nAfter the half of panel discussion, the audience could ask questions of their own for the panel. The first question probed the issue of able-bodied actors portraying people of disability and the opinion of the panel.\\n\\nDawn Jani Birley responded that it is unethical for such instance. She equated it to the issue of black face, where white actors portray black characters in untrue ways.\\n\\nBirley said that she would know who is not deaf, based on their performance and mediocre sign language.\\n\\nShe also relates this issue to the erasure of minority groups on popular media. Deaf community is rarely seen on TV. For deaf kids, they lack a role model to inspire them. And even with the current coverage of deaf community on mainstream media, Birley said that it didn\'t match with what she experienced in her life.\\n\\n\\"[...] deaf people are not tragedies\\", emphasized Birley.\\n\\nRepresentation is key. It is crucial that deaf people are viewed as celebrating role model for the future generations, according to Birley.\\n\\n## How to be better allies?\\n\\nThis begs the next question: \\"How can we do better as allies?\\"\\n\\nRead and Birley encouraged the audience in the room to challenge the assumptions. Allies should be willing to bear being wrong and they should be\xa0self aware. They should also check in and try to understand the community they\'re supporting.\\n\\nInstead of saying \\"I understand you\\", because the statement would ignore the struggles of minority groups, they should ask questions such as: \\"I want to support you in a suitable way. How can I help you?\\"\\n\\nAs society is recognizing the problems and issues of visibility and diversity, we are working towards a better future, one step at a time. Birley and Read recalls one of the beautiful moments when their audience\xa0tried to learn sign language. They appreciate the audience\'s effort to understand the language and communicate with them."}]}')}}]);